review:
I've had my iPad for 2 days now, here are a couple of impressions. First, I love the cover I was "Gifted" that I carry it in.<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Twelve-South-BookBook-for-iPad-in-Red/dp/B0042X8XC8/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Twelve South BookBook for iPad in Red</a>

Video watching;

I like the screen size and resolution of movies/TV shows. The audio quality is good without headphones (better with.) I also purchased the&nbsp;<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Apple-Composite-AV-Cable/dp/B001MKF8O0/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Apple Composite AV Cable</a>&nbsp;AV Cable, and watched&nbsp;<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Up-Single-Disc-Widescreen/dp/B001KVZ6FW/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Up (Single Disc Widescreen)</a>&nbsp;UP with my family. Crisp resolution, and easy hook-up.

Wi-Fi;
Decided NOT to buy 3G. Can't tell you yet if I regret. But--my thinking right now is, where do I go that there ISN'T wi-fi? I'm primarily going to use this at home, at work and traveling. When's the last time you went to a hotel without wifi? And, really, if there's no wifi, I can live for an hour or two 'till there is.

GUI;
Is pretty intuitive. Actually gave me a little vertigo at first, learned to organize "pages" so apps of similar apps are on similar pages. (I thought I would like folders, but it was too confusing.)

Web;
Safari browser is fine and crisp. Easy to use. I will list (as I'm sure others will) occasional frustration at lack of Flash solution. It has gotten in the way on more than a few web-sites.

Update from iPod Touch.<a data-hook="product-link-linked" class="a-link-normal" href="/Apple-iPod-touch-32-GB-4th-Generation-NEWEST-MODEL/dp/B001FA1O18/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_rvw_txt?ie=UTF8">Apple iPod touch 32 GB (4th Generation) NEWEST MODEL</a>
Was pretty easy. Apps all work on the new iPad, though in a diminished window. (You can click 2x to fill the screen, but with smaller resolution.) A few apps (Facebook) are actually better on the iPod Touch. Not sure I want to pay twice to download iPad versions of some games (Angry Birds, Scrabble)

So far, I'm deeply fond of my new iPad.
